SELinux workaround policy for lxc
=================================

Install the policy with:

  semodule -i lxc-rootfs.pp

NOTE:
The policy is a quick workaround. It's not a proper solution. Please don't
use it on a production system. I consider it marginally better than
setenforce 0.

type=AVC msg=audit(1442523531.083:5156): avc:  denied  { mounton } for  pid=13953 comm="lxc-start" path="/usr/lib64/lxc/rootfs/proc/1/net" dev="proc" ino=193884 scontext=unconfined_u:unconfined_r:unconfined_t:s0-s0:c0.c1023 tcontext=unconfined_u:unconfined_r:unconfined_t:s0-s0:c0.c1023 tclass=dir permissive=0

